WEBVTT

00:02.611 --> 00:04.917
♪

00:12.273 --> 00:15.145
[knocking on door]

00:15.189 --> 00:17.234
[gasps]

00:21.804 --> 00:23.023
[exhales]

00:27.070 --> 00:29.246
I'm sorry, Officer.

00:29.290 --> 00:31.118
If this is about the moaning

00:31.161 --> 00:32.989
coming from my dorm room
last night,

00:33.033 --> 00:34.817
it seems to have stopped.

00:34.860 --> 00:37.515
It's not. Is there
an adult I can speak to?

00:37.559 --> 00:39.387
Someone in charge?

00:39.430 --> 00:41.519
Sure.
My father's the headmaster.

00:41.563 --> 00:42.781
I'll go wake him up.

00:42.825 --> 00:46.220
You're Alaric Saltzman's
daughter?

00:46.263 --> 00:47.438
Yeah.

00:47.482 --> 00:50.485
One of them. Why?

00:50.528 --> 00:52.922
I'm afraid I have some bad news.

01:02.323 --> 01:04.368
[birds chirping in distance]

01:14.161 --> 01:16.206
[exhales]

01:16.250 --> 01:17.599
You scared me.

01:18.730 --> 01:19.905
I thought that you left.

01:19.949 --> 01:21.429
You gave me a whole speech about

01:21.472 --> 01:23.474
how you deserved better
than that, remember?

01:23.518 --> 01:25.737
Well, I'm glad
that it left an impression.

01:25.781 --> 01:29.176
So, what do you want
to do today?

01:31.091 --> 01:33.963
Cleo's back, thanks to you.

01:34.006 --> 01:36.052
So I think we should celebrate.

01:40.361 --> 01:42.319
LIZZIE [in distance]:Josie!

01:42.363 --> 01:44.104
What the hell was that?

01:44.147 --> 01:45.801
Lizzie.

01:47.150 --> 01:48.891
ETHAN:
Bad luck comes in threes, right?

01:48.934 --> 01:50.980
In my experience,

01:51.023 --> 01:53.069
it can be more than that.

01:53.113 --> 01:54.984
Why do you ask?Because from what

01:55.027 --> 01:56.203
you've told me,
the last two guys

01:56.246 --> 01:58.814
that crashed here are dead.

01:59.945 --> 02:02.818
Raf's still alive. Technically.

02:02.861 --> 02:05.037
And before this
place was a school,

02:05.081 --> 02:08.519
this room belonged to a vampire
by the name of Stefan Salvatore.

02:10.695 --> 02:11.914
Who died.

02:11.957 --> 02:13.785
Kind of like Landon,

02:13.829 --> 02:15.526
if Cleo's right about
what happened to him.

02:15.570 --> 02:17.180
Assuming she is,

02:17.224 --> 02:20.183
Landon made
the ultimate hero move.

02:20.227 --> 02:22.272
And he's number three.

02:25.275 --> 02:27.582
Athletes are
superstitious.

02:27.625 --> 02:30.019
Maybe that's why people
think we're dumb.

02:30.062 --> 02:31.934
We'll assign you
your permanent room

02:31.977 --> 02:34.197
after you talk to Dr. Saltzman.

02:36.199 --> 02:38.332
Hey. Man, I thought
you'd be more excited

02:38.375 --> 02:40.247
about us being Super Friends.

02:40.290 --> 02:42.423
Even if I don't know
what my powers actually are.

02:42.466 --> 02:44.207
We'll figure it out.

02:44.251 --> 02:46.209
I mean, you, me

02:46.253 --> 02:47.515
and Lizzie

02:47.558 --> 02:48.994
at the same school?

02:49.038 --> 02:50.648
What could go wrong?

02:50.692 --> 02:51.954
FINCH: MG.

02:51.997 --> 02:53.260
Lizzie needs you.

03:02.094 --> 03:04.140
KALEB: How long have
you been in here?

03:04.184 --> 03:06.055
Most of the night.

03:06.098 --> 03:08.536
Inspiration strikes
at strange times.

03:08.579 --> 03:11.321
I'm glad to hear that, 'cause
I could damn sure use some.

03:12.366 --> 03:13.845
You could not sleep, either?

03:13.889 --> 03:15.586
How could I? Thinking
about everything

03:15.630 --> 03:17.762
that happened
with Landon,

03:17.806 --> 03:19.634
how I handed Hope
over to Malivore

03:19.677 --> 03:22.114
and sold out the whole school
along with her.

03:22.158 --> 03:23.768
Just trying to
think of some way

03:23.812 --> 03:24.987
to make up for it.

03:25.030 --> 03:27.555
I miss Landon, too, but...

03:27.598 --> 03:29.252
I can't help him,

03:29.296 --> 03:31.254
so I'll help you.

03:31.298 --> 03:34.126
The only question is how?Yeah, I-I don't know.

03:34.170 --> 03:36.999
You j... I just figure you're
the expert on forgiveness.

03:37.042 --> 03:39.610
You know, I mean, you
straight-up tried to murder Hope

03:39.654 --> 03:41.525
and now, now you're
part of the Squad.

03:41.569 --> 03:43.484
So you...
[chuckles]

03:44.572 --> 03:47.096
I'm sorry. That was...

03:47.139 --> 03:48.706
Bad joke.

03:48.750 --> 03:50.839
You know, sometimes we
laugh so we don't cry.

03:50.882 --> 03:53.407
[laughs softly]
If you wish to be forgiven,

03:53.450 --> 03:55.887
you need only be honest
with your friends.

03:56.975 --> 03:59.239
Our friends.

04:00.588 --> 04:02.111
They will understand,

04:02.154 --> 04:04.505
as they did
when I told them my story.

04:07.377 --> 04:09.205
Let's go find them.

04:09.249 --> 04:11.512
See if you're right.

04:16.647 --> 04:18.388
LIZZIE:
This isn't right.

04:18.432 --> 04:20.216
Our father spends
practically his whole life

04:20.260 --> 04:22.044
protecting this town,
and now his life

04:22.087 --> 04:23.654
is in the hands of doctors
who aren't even smart enough

04:23.698 --> 04:26.091
to know what an actual
animal attack looks like.

04:26.135 --> 04:27.528
JOSIE:
Lizzie, I understand

04:27.571 --> 04:29.399
how hard this is,
but you need to calm down.

04:29.443 --> 04:30.531
How can you say
that when they are

04:30.574 --> 04:32.184
cutting into him right now?

04:32.228 --> 04:34.404
When Mr. Williams is in
Shanghai, visiting Emma?

04:34.448 --> 04:36.101
When Mom's halfway
down the Congo,

04:36.145 --> 04:38.495
ironically looking for a way
to save our lives?

04:38.539 --> 04:40.367
There's no need to answer that,
because MG's blood

04:40.410 --> 04:44.240
could fix whatever is wrong
with Dad in a second.

04:44.284 --> 04:46.111
If he makes it off the table.

04:50.725 --> 04:52.292
Lizzie,

04:52.335 --> 04:54.729
I hear you, okay?

04:54.772 --> 04:56.557
But so can everyone else.

04:56.600 --> 04:58.559
Who cares?
No one here takes us seriously.

04:58.602 --> 05:00.212
The staff won't even tell us
what's going on,

05:00.256 --> 05:01.910
except that our father
was assaulted.

05:01.953 --> 05:03.477
Maybe hit by a car.

05:03.520 --> 05:06.306
All we know is that he's
fighting for his life.

05:08.873 --> 05:11.006
We've already lost Landon.

05:12.921 --> 05:14.575
Dad's gonna pull through.

05:14.618 --> 05:17.012
There's no reason to think
of any other outcome.

05:17.055 --> 05:19.710
Okay?

05:19.754 --> 05:20.929
[door opens]

05:20.972 --> 05:22.670
MG.

05:24.019 --> 05:26.151
What did your
vamp ears hear?

05:26.195 --> 05:29.981
Dr. Saltzman is out
of surgery. He's stable.

05:30.025 --> 05:32.375
Thank God.
Okay, when can we see him?

05:32.419 --> 05:33.898
More importantly,
when can yousee him?

05:33.942 --> 05:35.335
Soon.

05:35.378 --> 05:37.424
But I don't think
I'm gonna be able to fix

05:37.467 --> 05:39.208
what's wrong with him.

05:40.252 --> 05:41.558
We just heard what happened.

05:41.602 --> 05:42.777
How's Doc doing?

05:43.995 --> 05:45.867
Where's Hope?

05:49.392 --> 05:50.959
Is there a problem or something?

05:51.002 --> 05:52.395
Several.

05:52.439 --> 05:54.049
None worth wasting my breath on.

05:56.486 --> 05:59.054
I didn't come here to talk,
either. I came here to drink.

06:01.099 --> 06:02.840
Grab me a bottle of tequila.

06:02.884 --> 06:04.929
I'm gonna need a chaser.

06:06.888 --> 06:09.499
♪

06:12.459 --> 06:13.677
You'll do.

06:16.332 --> 06:18.029
♪ Thought you'll change
the weather ♪

06:18.073 --> 06:21.119
♪ Start a little storm,
make a little rain ♪

06:21.163 --> 06:22.904
♪ But I'm gonna do one better

06:22.947 --> 06:25.820
♪ Have the sun until you pray

06:25.863 --> 06:27.082
♪ I'm a tornado

06:29.389 --> 06:32.435
♪ Looking for a soul to take

06:34.437 --> 06:35.438
♪ You're gonna see me...

06:35.482 --> 06:36.570
[grunts, laughs]

06:36.613 --> 06:38.920
So...

06:38.963 --> 06:40.225
you want another drink?

06:40.269 --> 06:41.662
♪ I'm gonna leave you guessing

06:41.705 --> 06:44.186
♪ How this funnel is gonna hit

06:44.229 --> 06:45.187
♪ I'm a tornado...

06:45.230 --> 06:46.623
I'll get it myself.

06:47.624 --> 06:50.105
REBEKAH:
Mind if I cut in?

06:56.633 --> 06:58.113
Who's this

06:58.156 --> 06:59.549
classy bitch?

07:01.029 --> 07:03.466
My Aunt Rebekah.

07:10.473 --> 07:13.389
It's been too long, little one.

07:14.869 --> 07:17.262
Thought you'd be happier
to see me.

07:17.306 --> 07:19.613
I was happy. And then I saw you.

07:20.527 --> 07:21.832
Look, lady,

07:21.876 --> 07:23.138
I know you have
a fancy accent and all,

07:23.181 --> 07:25.270
so maybe you don't get it.

07:26.228 --> 07:28.099
She don't seem to want you here.

07:28.143 --> 07:30.580
Yes, well, what I want

07:30.624 --> 07:32.452
is another song.

07:32.495 --> 07:34.584
Because you're right,
I'm a very fancy bitch,

07:34.628 --> 07:36.717
and country music
is for garbage people.

07:38.327 --> 07:39.763
Run along and change it,
will you?

07:39.807 --> 07:40.938
Sure.

07:40.982 --> 07:42.331
[country music playing]

07:46.074 --> 07:48.206
Freya told me what happened.

07:48.250 --> 07:50.513
Sorry I wasn't there
for your big day, but

07:50.557 --> 07:52.559
I'm here now.

07:52.602 --> 07:54.386
Shall we make up for lost time?

07:54.430 --> 07:56.606
How, a Mikaelson family lecture?

07:58.608 --> 08:01.437
Hope, this is my
worst nightmare.

08:01.481 --> 08:04.396
I always thought of myself
as the fun aunt, and yet,

08:04.440 --> 08:07.704
here you are,
looking at me like I'm an old.

08:09.271 --> 08:10.968
Dear God, please tell me
I used that right.

08:12.448 --> 08:14.755
Close enough. What kind of fun
did you have in mind?

08:14.798 --> 08:16.191
♪

08:16.234 --> 08:20.238
A drink, for starters.

08:20.282 --> 08:23.111
♪ Living dangerous,
don't need motivation ♪

08:23.154 --> 08:25.200
♪ Tearing up the check
and cashing glory... ♪

08:25.243 --> 08:26.375
[gasps]

08:26.418 --> 08:28.508
♪

08:33.469 --> 08:35.471
♪ Push on the cages, hey [grunting]

08:35.515 --> 08:37.691
♪ They might not like
what I'm saying ♪

08:37.734 --> 08:39.606
♪ Oh

08:39.649 --> 08:43.435
♪ This revolution
is knockin' at the door ♪

08:46.308 --> 08:47.744
♪ Burn the fuse...

08:47.788 --> 08:48.789
[panting]

08:48.832 --> 08:50.442
Weird first day, huh?

08:52.140 --> 08:54.577
Yeah. The weirdest.

08:54.621 --> 08:56.361
Thank you for the save.

08:59.060 --> 09:01.453
Why aren't you
at the hospital?

09:01.497 --> 09:03.325
Because sometimes,

09:03.368 --> 09:05.196
being in a relationship
with a Saltzman sister

09:05.240 --> 09:07.111
means realizing you aren't
a Saltzman sister.

09:08.635 --> 09:10.332
Besides, I hate hospitals.

09:11.072 --> 09:13.117
So take it easy in here, okay?

09:13.161 --> 09:15.076
How do you manage

09:15.119 --> 09:17.121
being with a Saltzman?

09:18.383 --> 09:20.037
Um...

09:20.081 --> 09:22.213
theoretically speaking.

09:22.257 --> 09:25.260
Are you seriously asking me
for romantic advice?

09:27.175 --> 09:29.917
I know that I gave you
a really hard time

09:29.960 --> 09:30.961
when you were dating Maya.

09:31.005 --> 09:32.615
But in my defense,

09:32.659 --> 09:34.225
I probably would have seen
things differently

09:34.269 --> 09:36.750
if I would have known
that you were a werewolf.

09:38.578 --> 09:39.796
Thanks.

09:42.320 --> 09:45.323
But are we theoretically talking
about Lizzie?

09:46.542 --> 09:48.109
Then damn, dude,
you do need help.

09:48.152 --> 09:50.111
I don't even know how
she feels about me,

09:50.154 --> 09:52.504
just that...

09:52.548 --> 09:54.332
I'd like
to do something for her.

09:54.376 --> 09:57.205
Let her know that she's
not alone in this.

09:57.248 --> 09:59.381
Well, when you put it that way,

09:59.424 --> 10:01.383
it seems like we have
the same problem.

10:01.426 --> 10:03.820
KALEB:
I got through to Finch.

10:03.864 --> 10:05.648
Hope's not at the school and...

10:05.692 --> 10:07.737
[indistinct announcement
over P.A.]

10:09.652 --> 10:12.916
And, obviously, I missed
something big while I was gone.

10:12.960 --> 10:15.440
Just a magic mirror call
with Professor Vardemus,

10:15.484 --> 10:17.921
who told us
what I was afraid of.

10:17.965 --> 10:19.706
Doc's in a coma.

10:19.749 --> 10:22.360
Our blood-- it can't
wake Dr. Saltzman up.

10:22.404 --> 10:24.536
And it turns out
the human brain

10:24.580 --> 10:26.060
doesn't heal so easy.

10:26.103 --> 10:28.366
It's the same way
with certain diseases.

10:28.410 --> 10:30.151
The doctors finally
came by, too.

10:30.194 --> 10:31.761
And they said
that we won't know

10:31.805 --> 10:34.459
what we're dealing with
until Dad wakes up.

10:34.503 --> 10:36.200
If.

10:38.855 --> 10:41.162
Perhaps there is a way
to wake Dr. Saltzman and learn

10:41.205 --> 10:42.293
what happened to him.

10:42.337 --> 10:43.555
How?

10:43.599 --> 10:44.774
Another vampire power.

10:44.818 --> 10:46.297
The same one
you used to reach me

10:46.341 --> 10:47.821
when I was trapped
in Malivore's mind.

10:47.864 --> 10:49.257
A head dive.

10:49.300 --> 10:51.607
She's right.
If I can get you two in there

10:51.651 --> 10:53.522
and you can find Doc, then...JOSIE: Then we might be able

10:53.565 --> 10:54.741
to bring him
back with us.

10:54.784 --> 10:56.525
LIZZIE:
It's a good plan.

10:56.568 --> 10:58.396
But for all we know, a monster
could have attacked Dad,

10:58.440 --> 10:59.441
so sorry, Kaleb, but I'm
not willing to trust someone

10:59.484 --> 11:01.443
who sold us out to Malivore.

11:04.925 --> 11:07.057
Guess that means it's up to you.

11:13.542 --> 11:15.718
I deserved every bit of that.

11:17.285 --> 11:19.330
I just wish there was
something I could do.

11:19.374 --> 11:21.855
Perhaps there is.
[chuckles]

11:21.898 --> 11:23.378
Because if Elizabeth is right

11:23.421 --> 11:25.032
and there's another monster
out there,

11:25.075 --> 11:27.208
Dr. Saltzman isn't the
only person you wronged

11:27.251 --> 11:28.818
who might be in danger.

11:28.862 --> 11:30.864
Or need help,
after what happened to Landon.

11:33.431 --> 11:35.085
I'm gonna find Hope.

11:36.565 --> 11:37.871
[indistinct chatter]

11:37.914 --> 11:39.481
Aren't you gonna
finish your drink?

11:39.524 --> 11:42.527
Yeah, I think
I'd better slow down.

11:42.571 --> 11:44.616
Maybe I'm an old after all.

11:44.660 --> 11:47.358
That's not the drink
I was talking about.

11:52.494 --> 11:54.278
I've had quite enough
of that.

11:54.322 --> 11:55.671
Besides, she's almost empty.

11:55.715 --> 11:57.107
So what?

11:57.151 --> 11:58.979
We can drain her dry,
pop another open.

11:59.022 --> 12:01.416
You said you wanted to have fun.

12:08.858 --> 12:11.513
Forget everything
that happened here today.

12:11.556 --> 12:15.430
Leave. But always remember
that country music is awful.

12:17.519 --> 12:20.391
I'm surprised you kept up
the act as long as you did.

12:20.435 --> 12:21.958
Must have been torture for you.

12:22.959 --> 12:25.701
What's torture is watching you
go through this on your own,

12:25.745 --> 12:27.355
when you have a family
who loves you

12:27.398 --> 12:29.966
and who has experienced
exactly what you are.

12:32.273 --> 12:34.405
Please come home with me.

12:34.449 --> 12:37.234
You have no idea
what I'm going through.

12:37.278 --> 12:38.366
What am I missing?

12:38.409 --> 12:39.976
Is being a Tribrid

12:40.020 --> 12:41.761
really that different
than being a vampire?

12:41.804 --> 12:44.851
This isn't about what
you're missing, Auntie Bex.

12:49.856 --> 12:51.205
Your humanity.

12:51.248 --> 12:53.511
♪

12:58.081 --> 13:00.127
[steady beeping]

13:04.218 --> 13:05.828
HOPE:
It's too late.

13:05.872 --> 13:07.612
My humanity switch
flipped the second

13:07.656 --> 13:09.266
that sword went through Landon.

13:09.310 --> 13:10.790
But I gotto say,

13:10.833 --> 13:13.575
it really seems
to be working for me.

13:13.618 --> 13:15.795
I got so sick of being
controlled by my emotions.

13:15.838 --> 13:18.710
It's like: love,
lose, grieve, repeat.

13:18.754 --> 13:20.974
I am finally free.

13:22.410 --> 13:25.239
So don't try to talk me out
of it. I'm not coming back.

13:25.282 --> 13:26.588
Then why did you
bring me here?

13:26.631 --> 13:28.372
To send a message.

13:28.416 --> 13:31.071
Make sure that my, um,
little friends stay away, too.

13:32.072 --> 13:34.552
Well, I don't think
they'll listen.

13:36.903 --> 13:38.861
I'll make it loud and clear.

13:42.343 --> 13:43.823
[shouts]

13:45.694 --> 13:48.088
[grunts]

13:48.131 --> 13:49.219
[grunts][groans]

13:50.220 --> 13:51.700
Hope, this isn't you.

13:51.743 --> 13:52.657
[grunting]

13:52.701 --> 13:53.963
Oh, it is.

13:54.007 --> 13:55.573
[grunting]

13:58.272 --> 13:59.403
[groans]

14:03.103 --> 14:04.931
[panting]

14:04.974 --> 14:06.584
I know you've been trying
to stop this from happening

14:06.628 --> 14:08.848
since I was a little girl,
but, uh...

14:10.371 --> 14:12.025
...you were
only holding me back.

14:12.068 --> 14:13.548
[chuckles softly]

14:13.591 --> 14:15.289
'Cause I finally realized...

14:16.681 --> 14:19.336
...I am my father's daughter.

14:27.214 --> 14:28.911
[cracking][groans]

14:34.221 --> 14:36.266
And I'm cool with that.

14:37.311 --> 14:38.921
Dad!

14:38.965 --> 14:40.314
Dad.

14:41.358 --> 14:42.882
Wake up, Dad.
[sniffles]

14:42.925 --> 14:44.796
We're here. Please.
[shuddering]

14:44.840 --> 14:46.363
I don't think
he can hear you.

14:47.364 --> 14:48.844
Because that's not him.

14:48.888 --> 14:50.541
This is just his last memory.

14:50.585 --> 14:52.717
Which means we know
who attacked him.

14:52.761 --> 14:54.284
That we need to warn
the others about...

14:54.328 --> 14:55.895
Screw Hope.

14:55.938 --> 14:57.331
[breathing heavily]

14:57.374 --> 14:59.724
If she was here right now,

14:59.768 --> 15:02.292
I would kill her.

15:02.336 --> 15:06.035
I don't think that's possible.

15:06.079 --> 15:07.950
A-And I don't think
you mean that.

15:07.994 --> 15:09.996
Doesn't matter.[cries]

15:10.039 --> 15:11.432
You heard her.

15:11.475 --> 15:13.347
Her humanity is off.

15:13.390 --> 15:15.915
And the last thing she wants
right now is to be around us.

15:15.958 --> 15:18.308
So if you want to
protect our friends,

15:18.352 --> 15:21.007
it's better if
they don't know.

15:21.050 --> 15:23.487
Because they'll go after her.

15:23.531 --> 15:26.142
And she'd probably
murder them, too.

15:26.186 --> 15:28.057
Stop saying that.
Dad's not dead.

15:28.101 --> 15:29.754
Well, then where is he?!I don't know.

15:29.798 --> 15:33.019
But we're in his mind,
so he has to be here somewhere.

15:36.848 --> 15:39.982
Those are just...
Memory Dad's.

15:40.026 --> 15:43.072
Those stupid boots Mom
got him for Christmas.

15:43.116 --> 15:45.770
I know. But in the memory,
he came from over there.

15:51.037 --> 15:53.430
What the hell went that way?

15:53.474 --> 15:56.259
His psyche? His soul?

15:58.435 --> 16:00.437
Only one way to find out.

16:03.701 --> 16:06.008
♪

16:14.669 --> 16:17.541
♪

16:18.586 --> 16:20.544
This isn't a memory.

16:20.588 --> 16:22.329
This is an
actual nightmare.

16:24.722 --> 16:27.943
Utter chaos, wanton destruction,

16:27.987 --> 16:29.423
borderline death.

16:30.380 --> 16:32.861
Our 11th birthday party.

16:32.904 --> 16:34.428
Though I remember it being

16:34.471 --> 16:35.951
pretty sweet.How?

16:35.995 --> 16:37.779
We got into a fight
with Dad

16:37.822 --> 16:39.955
because we invited
everybody but Hope.

16:39.999 --> 16:41.652
Then he brought her anyway,
and she turned

16:41.696 --> 16:43.263
our cake filling into worms.

16:43.306 --> 16:45.352
So you Motus'dher into
that bouncy house,

16:45.395 --> 16:46.396
and she tried to Incendia

16:46.440 --> 16:48.050
your party dress. So...

16:48.094 --> 16:50.183
I put up a shield spell
and it deflected hers

16:50.226 --> 16:51.923
and set our presents on fire.

16:51.967 --> 16:54.013
Did we really invite Wade?

16:54.056 --> 16:55.449
Lizzie, focus.

16:55.492 --> 16:57.233
Why would Dad want
to revisit this disaster?

16:57.277 --> 16:58.930
That's easy.

16:58.974 --> 17:01.063
This is the day he
realized that Hope is evil.

17:01.107 --> 17:03.326
He took our side
over hers for once.

17:03.370 --> 17:06.068
Remember? He took her
into his office for hours.

17:06.112 --> 17:08.070
The whole school
was gossiping about it.

17:08.114 --> 17:09.593
In my smallest moments,

17:09.637 --> 17:11.291
I used to dream
about what he said to her.

17:11.334 --> 17:12.422
Then you're about to find out.

17:12.466 --> 17:13.771
Because if you're right,

17:13.815 --> 17:15.773
that's where he should be.

17:19.864 --> 17:21.910
ALARIC:
I am so disappointed in you.

17:21.953 --> 17:24.043
Oh, good. We're
just in time.We're not.

17:24.086 --> 17:26.088
We're too late.
Look at his clothes.

17:26.132 --> 17:28.569
It's Memory Dad, not Dad Dad.
We need to keep going.Shh. I don't

17:28.612 --> 17:30.092
want to miss the best part.I mean, what you
did was irresponsible,

17:30.136 --> 17:31.485
reckless,

17:31.528 --> 17:32.921
violent, even.They started it.

17:32.964 --> 17:34.444
Hope, we have talked
about this

17:34.488 --> 17:36.403
so many times.It's not fair.

17:36.446 --> 17:37.621
They get to have
their own party.

17:37.665 --> 17:39.188
Their whole family comes.

17:39.232 --> 17:40.842
But yours can't.

17:41.799 --> 17:43.453
YOUNG HOPE:
They don't even remember me.But you're right--

17:43.497 --> 17:44.715
it's not fair.

17:44.759 --> 17:46.326
Oh, you have got
to be kidding me.

17:46.369 --> 17:47.849
Shh.YOUNG HOPE:
So what am I supposed to do

17:47.892 --> 17:49.416
when Lizzie and Josie
are mean to me?

17:49.459 --> 17:50.547
Be stronger than them.

17:50.591 --> 17:51.940
Because you are.

17:51.983 --> 17:52.941
HOPE:
What good is being strong

17:52.984 --> 17:54.551
if I have to hide it?

17:54.595 --> 17:57.467
Look, I know it's hard.
But only the strongest can.

17:58.512 --> 17:59.643
[sighs]

17:59.687 --> 18:01.123
Can I go back to my room now?

18:01.167 --> 18:03.125
I promise I won't
burn anything else.

18:03.169 --> 18:05.258
ALARIC:I have a different form
of discipline in mind.

18:05.301 --> 18:09.131
There's, um, a new art exhibit
at the museum in town.

18:09.175 --> 18:11.090
But I love art. It
reminds me of my dad.

18:11.133 --> 18:12.352
What kind?

18:12.395 --> 18:13.440
Modern.

18:13.483 --> 18:14.919
[scoffs]
That's stupid.

18:14.963 --> 18:17.226
Just blocks, lines and colors.

18:17.270 --> 18:18.923
[chuckles]

18:18.967 --> 18:20.708
Then maybe if you can find
the beauty in that,

18:20.751 --> 18:22.144
you'll be able to find
the beauty

18:22.188 --> 18:24.146
in what we've just
talked about, too.

18:25.191 --> 18:26.714
Can we get ice cream?

18:26.757 --> 18:27.845
Sure.

18:27.889 --> 18:29.195
But, uh,

18:29.238 --> 18:30.457
let's sneak out this way.LIZZIE: Okay,

18:30.500 --> 18:31.980
maybe you were right

18:32.023 --> 18:33.808
and we don't need
to be here. I mean,

18:33.851 --> 18:35.114
our dad is practically
on his deathbed

18:35.157 --> 18:36.593
and all he is thinking about

18:36.637 --> 18:38.117
is how he could have been
a better father

18:38.160 --> 18:39.596
to Hope Mikaelson,

18:39.640 --> 18:40.858
who freaking put him there.

18:40.902 --> 18:42.425
How does that make sense?

18:42.469 --> 18:43.948
I don't know.

18:43.992 --> 18:46.081
But we need to stick
to the plan and find Dad.

18:46.125 --> 18:48.039
Because if we don't,
we'll never understand.

18:48.083 --> 18:50.172
No other outcomes, remember?

18:50.216 --> 18:53.393
Fine. But where are we
supposed to go next?

18:53.436 --> 18:55.134
[buzz saw starts in distance]

18:57.223 --> 18:58.311
[retching]

18:58.354 --> 19:00.400
Oh, sweetheart. Let me help.

19:00.443 --> 19:01.923
I don't want your help.

19:01.966 --> 19:03.316
Why don't you get that?

19:03.359 --> 19:04.926
Because your humanity
is off.

19:04.969 --> 19:06.667
Which you explained to me
wasn't even your choice.

19:06.710 --> 19:08.321
It's the best thing
that's ever happened to me.

19:08.364 --> 19:10.192
No one craves tetanus
this much.

19:10.236 --> 19:11.889
What I crave is freedom.

19:11.933 --> 19:13.717
The ability to choose
my own fate, go wherever I want,

19:13.761 --> 19:15.154
be whoever I want.

19:15.197 --> 19:16.590
Forever.

19:16.633 --> 19:19.158
Such is the blessing
of immortality.

19:19.201 --> 19:20.637
And also the curse.

19:21.899 --> 19:23.771
When your emotions
are heightened,

19:23.814 --> 19:27.514
being a vampire can be
indescribably beautiful.

19:27.557 --> 19:30.125
The sights, the sounds--

19:30.169 --> 19:32.388
sadly, in this moment--
the smells... [sighs]

19:32.432 --> 19:36.131
all are beyond the limitations
of the human experience.

19:36.175 --> 19:38.699
But what's the point if
you don't appreciate it?

19:38.742 --> 19:40.135
I mean, you tell me.

19:40.179 --> 19:42.485
You're the one who wants
to be human again.

19:42.529 --> 19:45.836
I've lived as a vampire
for over a thousand years.

19:45.880 --> 19:48.752
I've experienced everything
the world has to offer.

19:49.753 --> 19:52.713
Except those experiences
that being a vampire

19:52.756 --> 19:54.193
makes impossible.

19:56.456 --> 19:59.110
I was envious
when Niklaus and Hayley

19:59.154 --> 20:00.634
had the miracle that is you.

20:02.810 --> 20:05.856
But I would gladly
give up that dream.

20:05.900 --> 20:07.728
I would give you the cure
if you wanted it.

20:07.771 --> 20:09.904
You're a hypocrite.

20:09.947 --> 20:11.732
So why don't you
stop trying to be a martyr

20:11.775 --> 20:14.561
like my father and go live
whatever life you want.

20:14.604 --> 20:17.085
Just let me do the same.

20:21.263 --> 20:23.134
You're right.

20:24.092 --> 20:27.051
[coughing]I am a hypocrite.

20:27.095 --> 20:29.619
I always hated it
when Niklaus did this to me.

20:31.795 --> 20:34.102
♪

20:43.764 --> 20:45.722
You're being a little extreme,
don't you think?

20:45.766 --> 20:47.855
I've already sent the
construction crew home, Emma.

20:47.898 --> 20:49.465
Because we can't
open this school

20:49.509 --> 20:51.293
if it means admitting
Hope Mikaelson,

20:51.337 --> 20:52.512
and you know it.

20:52.555 --> 20:53.730
I mean,
this psych evaluation

20:53.774 --> 20:54.818
you did on her--it has

20:54.862 --> 20:56.429
more red flags

20:56.472 --> 20:57.821
than a Georgia football game.Of course it does.

20:57.865 --> 20:59.345
She's a Mikaelson.

20:59.388 --> 21:00.694
But I thought
the point of this place

21:00.737 --> 21:02.304
is helping children like her.

21:02.348 --> 21:04.088
There is no one like her.

21:04.132 --> 21:05.960
This girl might be the most
powerful supernatural

21:06.003 --> 21:08.571
who ever existed, and
she's a ticking time bomb.

21:09.964 --> 21:11.400
I didn't write those words.

21:11.444 --> 21:13.489
Well, maybe not exactly.

21:13.533 --> 21:15.752
But tell me what happens,
in your professional opinion,

21:15.796 --> 21:18.842
if we take on this
risk and screw it up.

21:18.886 --> 21:20.844
Honestly?

21:20.888 --> 21:24.413
It would likely haunt us
for the rest of our lives.

21:24.457 --> 21:26.241
But far less than not trying.

21:26.285 --> 21:28.983
Think about all the good
Hope is capable of doing

21:29.026 --> 21:30.941
if we don't screw it up.

21:34.031 --> 21:35.729
My mind's made up.

21:35.772 --> 21:38.471
♪

21:42.779 --> 21:45.347
Great.

21:45.391 --> 21:47.958
[whirring][gasps] Ric!

21:48.002 --> 21:49.656
Memory Dad's a
real flip-flopper.

21:49.699 --> 21:51.571
But Hope's not the heroHelp!

21:51.614 --> 21:53.268
of this one, so at
least there's that.Ric, come back!

21:53.312 --> 21:55.270
How do you shut this off?What do you think changed

21:55.314 --> 21:57.794
his mind?I don't know.

21:57.838 --> 21:59.709
Maybe the next memory
will finally show us

21:59.753 --> 22:01.145
something useful.

22:01.189 --> 22:02.451
Help!

22:02.495 --> 22:03.409
Ric!

22:03.452 --> 22:04.888
[panting]

22:05.498 --> 22:06.847
We were hot on his heels.

22:06.890 --> 22:07.891
Why'd you
pull us out?

22:07.935 --> 22:08.805
I didn't.

22:09.415 --> 22:10.764
JOSIE:Oh, God.

22:10.807 --> 22:13.201
[rapid beeping]

22:13.244 --> 22:15.812
♪

22:32.002 --> 22:33.613
The doctors

22:33.656 --> 22:36.659
said that Dad had a
hemorrhagic stroke.

22:36.703 --> 22:38.618
Which is just
a fancy way of saying

22:38.661 --> 22:40.881
that his brain is bleeding.

22:40.924 --> 22:43.100
Um...

22:43.144 --> 22:45.625
how do they... fix that?

22:47.061 --> 22:48.628
They don't think that they can.

22:48.671 --> 22:51.413
His brain is still
showing signs of activity,

22:51.457 --> 22:54.329
and he may be able
to hear us for, um...

22:54.373 --> 22:55.635
a little while.

22:57.854 --> 23:00.204
I-I can't accept that.

23:00.248 --> 23:01.771
Your father

23:01.815 --> 23:03.773
has always taught us

23:03.817 --> 23:06.472
to try harder,
to be better than humans.

23:06.515 --> 23:08.648
So I wish
the timing were better

23:08.691 --> 23:10.867
on a lot of levels,
but all that means

23:10.911 --> 23:13.261
is we've been going
about this wrong.

23:13.304 --> 23:14.697
There's no point

23:14.741 --> 23:17.265
in you two following
your father around.

23:17.308 --> 23:19.180
We have to get you
ahead of him.

23:19.223 --> 23:20.573
How?

23:20.616 --> 23:23.053
He has a surprisingly
large brain.

23:23.097 --> 23:26.274
By figuring out where
exactly he'll go next.

23:26.317 --> 23:28.885
Isolating a memory that we know
he's going to visit...

23:30.539 --> 23:32.280
...before...At least

23:32.323 --> 23:34.195
we've narrowed it down.

23:34.238 --> 23:36.458
'Cause if there's one thing
we know, it'll be about Hope.

23:36.502 --> 23:38.199
Respectfully,

23:38.242 --> 23:39.983
I disagree.

23:41.768 --> 23:43.291
I think I know exactly

23:43.334 --> 23:45.119
where Dr. Saltzman's gonna go.

23:46.076 --> 23:47.600
'Cause I've been seeing all

23:47.643 --> 23:49.210
the same memories you guys have.

23:49.253 --> 23:50.864
Well,

23:50.907 --> 23:53.214
maybe one of us
should stay here.

23:53.257 --> 23:54.868
For Dad, just...

23:54.911 --> 23:56.478
in case, he, um...

24:00.308 --> 24:02.702
There's another outcome?

24:05.052 --> 24:06.749
[sighs]

24:09.012 --> 24:11.319
[inhales]
I don't want

24:11.362 --> 24:13.930
to be alone either.
[shudders]

24:19.545 --> 24:21.503
Then I'll go with you.

24:21.547 --> 24:24.114
♪

24:32.862 --> 24:36.126
Hey. You seriously gonna try to
bounce without paying your tab?

24:36.170 --> 24:37.911
I'll settle up with you
in a minute.

24:37.954 --> 24:40.000
And if you talk to me
like that again,

24:40.043 --> 24:41.958
what will be bouncing
is your h...

24:44.483 --> 24:46.485
♪

24:48.138 --> 24:49.357
BARTENDER:
Vampire aunt showed up.

24:49.400 --> 24:51.098
But I know-- I overstepped.

24:51.141 --> 24:53.274
That I was only supposed
to keep an eye on her.

24:53.317 --> 24:56.233
Turns out the Tribrid isn't
so hard to put down after all.

24:56.277 --> 24:58.627
WOMAN:
Never underestimate a Mikaelson.

24:58.671 --> 25:01.500
That's a problem
for the three of you.

25:01.543 --> 25:03.023
Though maybe it shouldn't be.

25:03.066 --> 25:04.720
If you're so scared of her...

25:04.764 --> 25:06.592
Just bring the girl to us.[beep]

25:08.028 --> 25:09.595
Right.

25:10.552 --> 25:12.946
[groaning]

25:13.990 --> 25:15.601
Scared yet?

25:21.258 --> 25:23.304
♪

25:38.362 --> 25:40.539
Shortest head dive ever.

25:40.582 --> 25:43.759
This was your big idea,
sending us ten feet?

25:45.413 --> 25:48.111
We went a lot further than that.

25:53.900 --> 25:56.293
This is Whitmore
Medical Center.

25:57.425 --> 25:59.383
Where Jo and
I were born.

26:01.124 --> 26:02.691
The day we were born.

26:04.171 --> 26:07.870
So, for the second time today,
happy birthday to me.

26:07.914 --> 26:09.611
But you still screwed up

26:09.655 --> 26:11.961
if you think my father
is gonna come here.

26:13.093 --> 26:14.094
[door opens]

26:14.137 --> 26:15.312
[footsteps approaching]

26:15.356 --> 26:16.400
[door closes]

26:20.491 --> 26:22.537
[shudders]
Elizabeth?

26:22.581 --> 26:25.888
♪

26:28.543 --> 26:30.284
[gasps]

26:30.327 --> 26:32.155
[chuckles]

26:32.199 --> 26:33.504
[sniffles]

26:33.548 --> 26:35.115
♪

26:39.685 --> 26:43.210
How'd you find me?I didn't.

26:46.692 --> 26:47.954
Thank you.

26:50.347 --> 26:51.610
Though, by the looks
on your faces,

26:51.653 --> 26:53.089
I'd say things
aren't going too well

26:53.133 --> 26:54.177
in the real world.

26:54.221 --> 26:56.745
So you know what's going on?

26:56.789 --> 26:59.705
Yeah, I remember what happened.

26:59.748 --> 27:03.012
Look, I don't mean
to sound corny here, but...

27:03.056 --> 27:06.189
I think my life's
flashing before my eyes.

27:06.233 --> 27:08.931
And there haven't been too many
highlights up to this point.

27:08.975 --> 27:12.500
But seeing you
sure makes up for it.

27:12.543 --> 27:14.415
Where's Jo?

27:14.458 --> 27:16.243
She wouldn't leave
your bedside.

27:16.286 --> 27:18.680
So, come back with us

27:18.724 --> 27:20.421
and you can see her, too.

27:20.464 --> 27:22.031
Oh, sweetie.

27:22.075 --> 27:24.730
[inhales]
I'm not sure I can.

27:31.954 --> 27:34.914
On the other side of this door,
I am holding you and your sister

27:34.957 --> 27:36.393
for the very first time.

27:38.221 --> 27:41.050
Giving you your names.

27:46.752 --> 27:48.579
It was, without question,

27:48.623 --> 27:51.365
the happiest day of my life.

27:52.366 --> 27:54.760
Why haven't you told us
about it before?

27:55.761 --> 27:57.763
[chuckles]:
Well...

27:57.806 --> 28:01.418
it was a complicated delivery.

28:01.462 --> 28:03.812
There was a huntress
and Heretics,

28:03.856 --> 28:06.685
you and your sister, siphoning
your mother from her womb.

28:12.865 --> 28:15.911
I guess I always thought
I had more time.

28:15.955 --> 28:18.784
[crackling]

28:18.827 --> 28:20.350
But I don't.

28:21.917 --> 28:23.745
So I...
[sniffles]

28:23.789 --> 28:26.748
I'd like to apologize
to you while I still can.

28:26.792 --> 28:28.141
BARTENDER:
I'm sorry!

28:28.184 --> 28:30.752
[groans, grunts]

28:30.796 --> 28:32.754
Then stop moving
so much.

28:32.798 --> 28:34.408
Bull's-eye is your eye.Don't you want to know

28:34.451 --> 28:35.539
why I'm here?

28:35.583 --> 28:37.106
Who sent me
to find you?

28:37.150 --> 28:38.673
Now that you mention it,
not really.

28:38.717 --> 28:40.153
Well,
you should.

28:40.196 --> 28:41.545
'Cause you're the hunted,
not the hunter.

28:41.589 --> 28:42.938
[chuckles softly]

28:42.982 --> 28:44.374
No. You see,

28:44.418 --> 28:46.202
I'm an apex predator.
Nobody hunts me.

28:46.246 --> 28:48.030
Except for maybe
my annoying aunt.

28:48.074 --> 28:49.379
I can prove it.

28:49.423 --> 28:50.511
Open my shirt.

28:50.554 --> 28:51.860
Oh, you're not really my type.

28:51.904 --> 28:53.819
Or maybe you're
the scared one.

28:54.820 --> 28:55.864
Hmm.

28:59.825 --> 29:01.261
Your tattoos
are awful.

29:01.304 --> 29:02.697
Especially that one.

29:02.741 --> 29:04.264
It's not a tattoo.
It's a brand.

29:04.307 --> 29:06.048
It's a mark of allegiance.To Triad.

29:06.092 --> 29:07.876
You're a little late. I shut
that place down a while ago.

29:07.920 --> 29:10.052
It's not a place.
It's three people.

29:10.096 --> 29:11.967
I'm talking
about the original bloodlines.

29:12.011 --> 29:14.578
Vampires, witches, werewolves,

29:14.622 --> 29:16.493
all united by
a single purpose.

29:16.537 --> 29:18.147
To kill monsters.
You see, Malivore's dead.

29:18.191 --> 29:19.496
Like I said, a little late.

29:19.540 --> 29:21.107
You're their
purpose, Tribrid.

29:21.150 --> 29:22.935
A new breed of monster
in their eyes.

29:22.978 --> 29:24.284
Destroying you is the only thing

29:24.327 --> 29:25.938
that all three factions
agree on.

29:26.939 --> 29:28.331
That's flattering.

29:28.375 --> 29:30.333
Maybe once they see
what I've done to you,

29:30.377 --> 29:31.944
they'll leave me alone.

29:33.989 --> 29:36.122
Wait, wait, wait, wait!
You can't kill me.

29:36.165 --> 29:37.558
No, I'm going to. I'm
literally doing it right now.

29:37.601 --> 29:39.255
But I'll take you to them!

29:39.299 --> 29:42.345
Has anybody ever told you
you're not a great henchman?

29:42.389 --> 29:45.348
All the time. Look, those idiots
treat me like crap.

29:45.392 --> 29:46.697
If you kill them,
we'll both be free.

29:46.741 --> 29:48.351
You want to make a deal?

29:48.395 --> 29:50.527
Tell me their names,
I'll make it quick.

29:50.571 --> 29:52.486
The person you should
be looking for is...

29:52.529 --> 29:55.097
[groaning]

29:55.141 --> 29:57.926
[yelling]

29:57.970 --> 30:00.146
[groaning]

30:00.189 --> 30:02.626
[screams]

30:02.670 --> 30:04.585
LIZZIE:
I don't understand.

30:06.500 --> 30:08.632
What do you want
to apologize for?

30:08.676 --> 30:10.896
For failing you and your sister.

30:10.939 --> 30:13.812
[sniffles]All these memories,

30:13.855 --> 30:15.422
the school,

30:15.465 --> 30:18.381
my whole life after this day
became about one thing--

30:18.425 --> 30:20.340
protecting the both of you

30:20.383 --> 30:21.907
and making sure
you remain protected,

30:21.950 --> 30:23.212
even after I was gone.

30:24.257 --> 30:25.867
MG:
That's why you
changed your mind.

30:25.911 --> 30:28.783
Why you let Hope join
the Salvatore School.

30:30.132 --> 30:31.786
ALARIC:
You know, at first,

30:31.830 --> 30:34.310
all I could think about
was how big of a risk it was.

30:34.354 --> 30:36.095
How her turning out
to be like her father

30:36.138 --> 30:39.228
would hurt you or Josie
or anyone else at the school.

30:44.233 --> 30:46.627
You know, but then I just
started seeing it another way.

30:46.670 --> 30:49.021
I figured
if you both turned out

30:49.064 --> 30:52.459
as well as you have
in spite of being raised by me,

30:52.502 --> 30:54.287
so could she.

30:54.330 --> 30:57.420
You know, I saw a world where
the three of you became friends.

30:59.074 --> 31:00.815
Family.

31:00.859 --> 31:02.556
The kind that would do
anything for each other,

31:02.599 --> 31:04.819
you know, in case something
happened to your mother or me.

31:04.863 --> 31:06.647
You know, uh,
she would protect you

31:06.690 --> 31:08.040
and you would protect her,
you know,

31:08.083 --> 31:09.476
in case I got myself killed.

31:09.519 --> 31:10.607
Or worse...

31:12.435 --> 31:14.307
...let you down.

31:14.350 --> 31:16.352
Which I have.[crackling]

31:19.486 --> 31:21.880
So please forgive me,
Lizzie.

31:24.143 --> 31:25.971
[shudders]
And you, too, Milton,

31:26.014 --> 31:27.973
for the danger
I've put you in.

31:28.016 --> 31:30.453
I-I don't think I have to.

31:30.497 --> 31:33.456
I've made plenty
of mistakes, too.

31:33.500 --> 31:35.502
But if you do,

31:35.545 --> 31:39.549
if you need that, of course
I forgive you, Dr. Saltzman.

31:41.073 --> 31:42.726
Well, I don't.

31:42.770 --> 31:45.425
I refuse.

31:45.468 --> 31:49.951
Because that way lies
rainbows and puppies and...

31:49.995 --> 31:51.170
peace.

31:51.213 --> 31:53.563
So you can forget

31:53.607 --> 31:55.957
about walking off
into the light.

31:56.001 --> 31:58.699
Or disappearing
into the darkness or whatever.

32:00.396 --> 32:02.485
You need to come
back with us.

32:02.529 --> 32:04.487
Right now.

32:04.531 --> 32:06.141
You have to make up
for all of it.

32:06.185 --> 32:09.318
You have to apologize to Josie.

32:09.362 --> 32:10.972
Do you hear me?

32:11.016 --> 32:13.105
Always.

32:13.148 --> 32:15.150
[crackling]

32:17.022 --> 32:18.284
[sniffles]

32:19.372 --> 32:20.764
But just in case...

32:20.808 --> 32:22.984
I'm sorry
for when I wasn't there

32:23.028 --> 32:25.160
for you and your sister.

32:25.204 --> 32:26.509
You know,
for all the times

32:26.553 --> 32:28.120
I prioritized Hope
or being headmaster

32:28.163 --> 32:31.253
over... being your father.

32:32.515 --> 32:34.909
For not telling you more often
how perfect I think

32:34.953 --> 32:37.259
you both are in my eyes.

32:39.348 --> 32:40.959
And all the flaws
that you think you have

32:41.002 --> 32:42.612
are what make you
that way.

32:42.656 --> 32:43.962
[crackling]

32:45.528 --> 32:46.486
[sniffles]

32:46.529 --> 32:48.662
And I-I'm sorry for...

32:48.705 --> 32:52.840
for leaving you in a world
more dangerous than before,

32:52.883 --> 32:56.104
when all I wanted to do
was make it safer.

32:59.542 --> 33:01.936
But I know you'll figure it out.

33:01.980 --> 33:04.765
Better than I could.

33:08.203 --> 33:10.205
I love you.

33:10.249 --> 33:13.382
♪

33:13.426 --> 33:15.732
And you take care of each other,
no matter what.

33:17.517 --> 33:18.692
You promise me.

33:18.735 --> 33:20.128
Daddy.

33:26.700 --> 33:28.919
How did you know
Hope would be here?

33:28.963 --> 33:31.574
Ain't hard. Place
reeks of blood.

33:32.575 --> 33:34.577
And smoke.

33:35.839 --> 33:37.798
We're too late.

33:38.799 --> 33:40.801
Not just for this dude.

33:40.844 --> 33:42.237
Hope's gone.

33:42.281 --> 33:44.065
CLEO:
Then we must find her
another way.

33:44.109 --> 33:46.720
But I'll have you know this does
not count as our first date.

33:48.939 --> 33:50.724
Sometimes we laugh
so we don't cry.

33:52.117 --> 33:54.075
I just don't get how
you stay so positive.

33:54.119 --> 33:58.514
Mm. I've overcome many things
others would think impossible.

33:58.558 --> 34:00.473
And until recently,

34:00.516 --> 34:02.083
I had to do so alone.[clinking]

34:02.127 --> 34:03.824
Forgive me if this way,

34:03.867 --> 34:06.305
having you here, seems easier.

34:06.348 --> 34:08.916
No matter how daunting
our task may be.

34:11.788 --> 34:13.051
Cool.

34:13.094 --> 34:15.270
'‘Cause I'm not
going anywhere.

34:16.576 --> 34:18.056
Then we must seal this pact.

34:20.101 --> 34:21.320
Yeah.

34:21.363 --> 34:23.017
This is how we do it
where I'm from.

34:26.325 --> 34:29.502
Sometimes,
the old ways are better.

34:31.069 --> 34:33.071
♪

34:36.987 --> 34:38.250
Is this a bad time?

34:39.251 --> 34:40.817
The worst.

34:40.861 --> 34:43.516
Lizzie and Josie are
staying with Dr. Saltzman

34:43.559 --> 34:46.127
until visiting
hours are over.

34:46.171 --> 34:48.347
His body's stable.

34:50.044 --> 34:52.090
But his mind is just gone.

34:53.700 --> 34:55.571
Damn.

34:58.052 --> 34:59.575
[exhales]

34:59.619 --> 35:01.795
Look, I know
it's my first day, but...

35:01.838 --> 35:03.623
Finch and I wanted
to do something.

35:03.666 --> 35:06.016
If you think it's a good idea.

35:08.323 --> 35:10.934
♪

35:16.897 --> 35:19.856
Uh, what I think

35:19.900 --> 35:23.077
is that the school is already
better for having you here.

35:25.210 --> 35:27.516
But I need to tell
you something.

35:27.560 --> 35:30.606
And the timing sucks
on this one, too.

35:31.607 --> 35:33.392
It's about Lizzie.MG.

35:34.741 --> 35:37.135
I know you're the other guy.

35:37.178 --> 35:39.702
You... you do?

35:39.746 --> 35:43.184
Lizzie told me that she had
this will-they-won't-they thing.

35:43.228 --> 35:45.273
And... when she needed help,

35:45.317 --> 35:48.015
the first thing anyone did
was come find you.

35:52.150 --> 35:55.457
Is that gonna make things...
weird

35:55.501 --> 35:57.111
between us?

35:57.155 --> 35:58.591
Because the
day's gonna come

35:58.634 --> 36:01.898
where I tell her
exactly how I feel.

36:05.815 --> 36:08.166
Then we'll jump off that cliff
when we get to it.

36:09.602 --> 36:11.821
But until then--
and hopefully after--

36:11.865 --> 36:14.215
I don't see why
we can't keep being friends.

36:15.912 --> 36:17.044
Super friends.

36:17.087 --> 36:18.350
[chuckles]

36:18.393 --> 36:20.917
♪

36:27.054 --> 36:28.969
I should have
been there.

36:29.970 --> 36:31.841
All I could do

36:31.885 --> 36:36.585
was watch
as he slowly slipped away to...

36:37.934 --> 36:39.893
...wherever he went.

36:41.373 --> 36:42.939
And I should've told you

36:42.983 --> 36:45.072
that I wanted you
to stay behind instead.

36:47.248 --> 36:48.641
But I didn't.

36:48.684 --> 36:51.078
And I need to get better
at things like that.

36:51.121 --> 36:54.124
Because when I don't, they
have a way of staying with me.

36:59.304 --> 37:01.958
I'm sorry.

37:02.002 --> 37:04.439
I'm selfish.

37:04.483 --> 37:06.572
And I don't say that enough.

37:08.791 --> 37:11.490
I guess the apple doesn't fall
too far from the tree.

37:14.493 --> 37:16.538
Forgive me.

37:19.759 --> 37:24.459
I promise I will find
a way to bring Dad back.

37:28.942 --> 37:31.901
♪ Be still and know

37:31.945 --> 37:35.427
♪ That I'm with you

37:35.470 --> 37:38.517
♪ Be still and know

37:38.560 --> 37:41.824
♪ That I am here

37:41.868 --> 37:45.306
♪ Be still and know

37:45.350 --> 37:48.483
♪ That I'm with you

37:48.527 --> 37:52.008
♪ Be still, be still

37:52.052 --> 37:53.532
♪ And know

37:55.229 --> 37:58.537
♪ When darkness comes

37:58.580 --> 38:01.322
♪ Upon you

38:01.366 --> 38:04.804
♪ And colors you

38:04.847 --> 38:08.242
♪ With fear and shame

38:08.286 --> 38:11.898
♪ Be still and know

38:11.941 --> 38:14.770
♪ That I'm with you

38:14.814 --> 38:16.381
♪ And I

38:16.424 --> 38:20.515
♪ Will say your name

38:20.559 --> 38:24.737
♪ If you forget

38:24.780 --> 38:28.393
♪ The way to go

38:28.436 --> 38:31.047
♪ And lose where you

38:31.091 --> 38:34.877
♪ Came from

38:34.921 --> 38:38.707
♪ If no one is standing

38:38.751 --> 38:42.189
♪ Beside you

38:42.232 --> 38:43.625
♪ Be still

38:43.669 --> 38:47.934
♪ And know I am

38:48.978 --> 38:52.373
♪ Be still and know

38:52.417 --> 38:55.942
♪ That I'm with you

38:55.985 --> 38:57.726
♪ Be still

38:57.770 --> 38:59.380
♪ And know

38:59.424 --> 39:00.990
♪ I am.

39:01.034 --> 39:02.165
Oh...

39:05.125 --> 39:07.388
Well, this is gonna be awkward.

39:10.173 --> 39:11.740
Were you really just
gonna leave me here,

39:11.784 --> 39:14.526
dumped on the side of the road
like garbage?

39:14.569 --> 39:16.310
Well, my first instinct was
to leave you in the alley.

39:18.486 --> 39:20.836
We're still family, Hope.

39:20.880 --> 39:23.752
What good is family if they
just stab you in the back?

39:28.235 --> 39:30.803
Doesn't work too well
on a Tribrid, FYI.

39:31.804 --> 39:33.762
I had to try.

39:33.806 --> 39:35.764
Nik would have.He's dead.

39:35.808 --> 39:37.766
And you know what killed him?

39:37.810 --> 39:39.202
Family.

39:39.246 --> 39:40.856
Love.

39:40.900 --> 39:42.205
Me.

39:43.337 --> 39:46.296
So maybe you should try
to stop being like him.

39:48.255 --> 39:50.866
You'd do well
taking your own advice.

39:50.910 --> 39:52.390
That was a warning.

39:52.433 --> 39:53.913
So if care about our family,

39:53.956 --> 39:55.175
stay away from me.

39:56.698 --> 39:59.353
Because I am
my father's daughter.

39:59.397 --> 40:01.834
But I'm not gonna make
the same mistakes.

40:03.618 --> 40:05.751
He'd be so ashamed.

40:08.275 --> 40:09.407
Don't go.

40:13.411 --> 40:15.369
This is how you
found me, isn't it?

40:18.154 --> 40:20.809
It's spelled. Probably by Freya.

40:22.985 --> 40:24.204
You keep it.

40:29.644 --> 40:31.820
Always and forever.

40:32.995 --> 40:34.475
I'll keep your car.

40:34.519 --> 40:36.129
♪

40:47.923 --> 40:49.534
[phone rings, beep]

40:49.577 --> 40:51.231
WOMAN:
Where are you?

40:51.274 --> 40:53.842
Jinx. I was about to ask you
the same question.

40:53.886 --> 40:56.715
Hope Mikaelson.

40:56.758 --> 40:58.760
Speaking. And you are?

40:58.804 --> 41:01.502
Oh, that would spoil the fun.

41:01.546 --> 41:04.287
Well, I just wanted your Triad
or whatever to know

41:04.331 --> 41:06.028
that I'm coming for you,

41:06.072 --> 41:07.377
whoever you are.

41:07.421 --> 41:08.596
Not soon enough.

41:08.640 --> 41:11.251
I'll be waiting.[click]
